################################################################################
########    An in silico target identification using boolean network    ########
########          attractors: avoiding pathological phenotypes          ########
################################################################################

How to:
    1) read my article (preprint version available at
    http://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01024788 and
    http://arxiv.org/abs/1407.4374), at least the Method section
    1) clone the project in your home directory ~/
    2) open the template file ~/kali-targ/example_network.f95

The example network is a boolean model of the mammalian cell cycle [1].

[1] Faur√©, A., Naldi, A., Chaouiya, C., & Thieffry, D. (2006). Dynamical
analysis of a generic Boolean model for the control of the mammalian cell cycle.
Bioinformatics, 22(14), e124-e131.

The algorithm was firstly implemented in Octave
(https://www.gnu.org/software/octave/) for convenience and then in Fortran 95
compiled with GFortran (https://www.gnu.org/software/gcc/fortran/) for
performance. The GNU Octave implementation is available in the octave folder of
the present project.
